  "prompt": "How does puberty change your face?",
  "response": "Puberty brings about significant changes to the face due to hormonal shifts, growth spurts, and the maturation of facial features. Here are the key ways puberty can change your face:\n\n### 1. **Bone Structure Changes**\n   - **Jawline and Chin:** The jawbone becomes more pronounced and angular in males, while females may develop a softer, more rounded jawline.\n   - **Cheekbones:** Cheekbones may become more prominent as the facial bones grow and reshape.\n   - **Forehead and Brow Ridge:** In males, the brow ridge (the bone above the eyes) may become more pronounced, giving a more defined forehead.\n\n### 2. **Skin Changes**\n   - **Oil Production:** Increased hormones (androgens) lead to higher oil production, which can cause acne or oily skin.\n   - **Skin Texture:** The skin may become thicker and more textured.\n\n### 3. **Facial Hair (More Prominent in Males)**\n   - Males typically develop facial hair, including mustaches, beards, and sideburns, due to rising testosterone levels.\n   - Females may experience some fine facial hair, but it is usually less noticeable.\n\n### 4. **Nose and Ears**\n   - **Nose:** The nose may grow larger and more defined, often becoming one of the first facial features to mature.\n   - **Ears:** The ears may also grow larger, often reaching their adult size earlier than other facial features.\n\n### 5. **Fat Distribution**\n   - **Males:** Fat tends to decrease in the face, leading to a more angular and defined appearance.\n   - **Females:** Fat may distribute to the cheeks and around the jawline, creating a softer, rounder face.\n\n### 6. **Facial Proportions**\n   - The face grows in proportion to the rest of the body, with the lower half of the face (jaw and chin) often showing the most noticeable growth.\n   - The eyes may appear smaller in relation to the rest of the face as other features grow.\n\n### 7. **Expression and Maturity**\n   - The face begins to look more mature as it loses its \"childish\" roundness and gains adult-like features.\n\n### 8. **Hormonal Effects on Features**\n   - Estrogen in females contributes to smoother skin and a more balanced facial appearance.\n   - Testosterone in males leads to broader, more angular features.\n\nThese changes vary from person to person, influenced by genetics, ethnicity, and overall health. While some changes happen quickly, others develop gradually over several years.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
